    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>basmati rice </strong>and 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has been absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sticky-chinese-style-basa-with-sesame-pak-choi-and-spring-onions/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, wash, then trim the base from your <strong>pak choi</strong>, then separate the individual leaves and discard the base</p><p>Trim your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong>, then cut each<strong> </strong>spring onion into thirds</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sticky-chinese-style-basa-with-sesame-pak-choi-and-spring-onions/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>hoisin sauce</strong> and <strong>honey</strong> to a bowl and give everything a good mix \u2013 this is your <strong>sticky sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sticky-chinese-style-basa-with-sesame-pak-choi-and-spring-onions/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>basa fillet[s]</strong> and cook for an initial 3-4 min on one side</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sticky-chinese-style-basa-with-sesame-pak-choi-and-spring-onions/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a separate large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick, with a matching lid) over medium heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>pak choi leaves</strong>, <strong>spring onion thirds </strong>and a small pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook, covered, for 3-4 min or until both have softened</p><p>Once softened, add the<strong> chopped garlic</strong> and your<strong> toasted sesame oil</strong> and cook for 1 min further \u2013 this is your <strong>sesame pak choi & spring onions</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sticky-chinese-style-basa-with-sesame-pak-choi-and-spring-onions/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>After 3-4 min turn the <strong>basa fillet[s]</strong> and add the <strong>sticky sauce </strong>to the pan</p><p>Cook for a further 3-4 min or until the basa is cooked through and the sauce has thickened to a sticky consistency \u2013 this is your <strong>sticky Chinese-style basa</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sticky-chinese-style-basa-with-sesame-pak-choi-and-spring-onions/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>black sesame seeds </strong>to the <strong>basmati</strong> <strong>rice</strong> and fluff with a fork \u2013 this is your <strong>sesame rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sticky-chinese-style-basa-with-sesame-pak-choi-and-spring-onions/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> sticky Chinese-style basa</strong> over the<strong> sesame rice </strong>and drizzle with any <strong>remaining sticky sauce</strong></p><p>Serve the<strong> sesame pak choi & spring onions</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
